179
00:13:54,470 --> 00:13:56,020
W-Who is it?!

180
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:06,190
He better run - that old man!

181
00:14:06,190 --> 00:14:08,860
That's Naguri from Gray Terminal!

182
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:11,600
Run! He's coming to you!

183
00:14:17,410 --> 00:14:19,460
What're you doing, old man?!

184
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:48,630
You know that you don't belong here!

185
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:52,660
Go back to the forest now!

186
00:15:09,290 --> 00:15:10,630
Cool!

187
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:18,390
It's like that time before!

188
00:15:36,810 --> 00:15:41,330
What?! You were a pirate
and a captain, Naguri?!

189
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:45,590
Yes, indeed.

190
00:15:45,590 --> 00:15:51,780
I knew it! Only a pirate
captain could do that!

191
00:15:51,780 --> 00:15:52,880
"That"?

192
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:58,520
You made the big bear turn away
just by staring at him like Shanks!

193
00:15:58,520 --> 00:16:00,730
You're cool, old man!

194
00:16:00,730 --> 00:16:02,560
You think so?

195
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:09,200
I can't believe that Naguri
was a pirate because...

196
00:16:11,050 --> 00:16:16,910
He's always collecting junk, hammering
away at them all day long,

197
00:16:16,910 --> 00:16:19,620
making weird stuff,

198
00:16:20,330 --> 00:16:22,530
and getting teased by the people

199
00:16:22,530 --> 00:16:26,640
at the Gray Terminal and by Bluejam's crew.

200
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:28,880
He looked pathetic.

201
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:32,510
You know nothing, Sabo!
That's how pirates are!

202
00:16:32,510 --> 00:16:34,640
You don't know anything, either!

203
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:36,850
What do you know about pirates?!

204
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:41,940
I know pirates! Shanks doesn't
do needless killings!

205
00:16:41,940 --> 00:16:43,640
Shanks, again.

206
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:45,480
Hey, it's cooked.

207
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,820
--Ow, ow, ow...!
--Ouch!

208
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:50,860
Oh, you got more than me!

209
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:52,980
You got to pay attention.

210
00:16:56,410 --> 00:16:59,160
Have some, Naguri. You helped us.

211
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:01,520
Oh, thank you.

212
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:07,210
So, what is a pirate captain
doing in a place like this?

213
00:17:10,210 --> 00:17:12,920
How could you ask me that?

214
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:16,300
You don't have to answer
if you don't want to.

215
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:18,760
No, I'll tell you.

216
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:22,680
Do you guys know Gold Roger?

217
00:17:24,350 --> 00:17:25,690
Roger?

218
00:17:25,690 --> 00:17:28,400
I know him! He was the King of the Pirates!

219
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:32,360
We challenged Roger, the King
of the Pirates, to a fight!

220
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:33,320
Really?!

221
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:38,310
But we lost the fight and split up.

222
00:17:40,330 --> 00:17:44,410
And everything just went downhill after that

223
00:17:44,410 --> 00:17:46,320
and I ended up like this.

224
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:50,880
That's basically what happened.

225
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:55,480
But you fought with the King of
the Pirates, right? That's cool!

226
00:17:56,170 --> 00:18:00,260
No, no, we were no match for him.

227
00:18:00,260 --> 00:18:04,020
We got beaten badly.

228
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:09,520
Oh really? Even you were no
match - that's how much he...

229
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:17,110
Yes. And not just Roger, his
crew was also very strong!

230
00:18:17,110 --> 00:18:22,580
Most importantly, their teamwork
was in perfect coordination!

231
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:26,250
It was our honor to fight with them.

232
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:35,460
I see! I still have a long
way to go to become a pirate.

233
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:39,010
Are you interested in pirates?

234
00:18:39,010 --> 00:18:42,390
--I'm gonna become one!
--Become a pirate?

235
00:18:42,390 --> 00:18:47,730
Yes, a pirate! Oh yeah, old pirate
man, could you give me some tips?!

236
00:18:48,690 --> 00:18:50,830
I want to get stronger!

237
00:18:50,830 --> 00:18:54,230
I have to become a captain
to lead Ace and Sabo!

238
00:18:54,230 --> 00:18:55,820
A captain?

239
00:18:55,820 --> 00:18:57,990
Hey, say yes! You're a pirate master!

240
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:01,740
--Okay!
--Okay?!

241
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:05,990
Yeah! Then, let's start from tomorrow!

242
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:10,250
Where did Ace go?!

243
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:13,040
Yeah, about that...

244
00:19:14,210 --> 00:19:15,880
What?!

245
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:18,260
The King of the Pirates is his father?!

246
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:22,260
Yeah. But you can't tell anybody.

247
00:19:22,260 --> 00:19:26,600
Don't mention it to Ace. He's gonna kill you.

248
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,970
Why?

249
00:19:27,970 --> 00:19:31,850
I don't know why but he
doesn't like Roger for sure.

250
00:19:31,850 --> 00:19:34,110
But that's his father, right?

251
00:19:34,110 --> 00:19:36,770
So what?

252
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:44,200
I'm sorry for both of you but I was
all by myself even if I had parents!

253
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:46,700
Oh yeah. Your parents...

254
00:19:47,370 --> 00:19:51,290
Children don't always get
along with their parents.

255
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:55,460
But, what a shame! He's
the King of the Pirates!

256
00:19:55,460 --> 00:19:59,240
I can understand that you
wanna ask him about Roger

257
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,960
but just don't, okay?

258
00:20:02,590 --> 00:20:04,640
Uh-huh! I got it!

259
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:06,350
And... you too, Naguri.

260
00:20:06,790 --> 00:20:08,910
Okay, I got it.

261
00:20:09,770 --> 00:20:14,570
But I can't believe that
that boy is Roger's son...

262
00:20:15,980 --> 00:20:21,360
There he is. Hey, just act casually.

263
00:20:21,360 --> 00:20:22,200
Yeah.

264
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:25,160
--Don't mention...
--I know! Don't worry!

265
00:20:27,740 --> 00:20:30,870
Oh, Ace! I didn't know that you were home!

266
00:20:30,870 --> 00:20:35,000
Oh, Ace! I didn't know that
your father was Roger!

267
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:38,170
I knew he'd say it!

268
00:20:38,170 --> 00:20:42,920
You idiot, Luffy! I told
you to not to mention it!

269
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:45,430
--Luffy!
--Yeah!

270
00:20:45,430 --> 00:20:47,430
Who told you that?

271
00:20:49,510 --> 00:20:51,390
Sabo told me!

272
00:20:51,390 --> 00:20:54,600
Hey Ace, what was Roger like?!

273
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:55,480
No!

274
00:20:55,480 --> 00:20:57,780
How stupid are you? Don't
just say it casually!

275
00:20:57,780 --> 00:21:00,440
Let me go! I am acting casually.

276
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:03,450
--Ouch!
--Ouch!

277
00:21:04,450 --> 00:21:08,120
Don't you ever mention
that name when I'm around!

278
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:13,830
Why did you hit me?!
Don't be mean - just tell me!

279
00:21:13,830 --> 00:21:16,420
Give people a chance to explain first!

280
00:21:16,420 --> 00:21:17,580
Shut up!

281
00:21:20,630 --> 00:21:22,340
Tell us about him! You're so mean!

282
00:21:22,340 --> 00:21:26,570
He's right! You can't have
a secret from your brothers!

283
00:21:26,570 --> 00:21:28,680
Shut up! I don't care about my brothers!

284
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:32,520
Roger, Roger, Roger! Ace's father
is the King of the Pirates!

285
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:35,310
Shut up! Don't provoke him!

286
00:21:35,980 --> 00:21:39,150
When you get down to it, it's
your fault for being a bigmouth!

287
00:21:39,150 --> 00:21:41,440
Ouch! What did you say?!

288
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:42,820
What are you doing?!

289
00:21:49,370 --> 00:21:53,580
We're no longer brothers from today!

290
00:21:53,580 --> 00:21:57,150
--That's what I was gonna say!
--That's what I was gonna say!

291
00:22:01,860 --> 00:22:04,500
Alright, I'm counting on you.

292
00:22:05,170 --> 00:22:09,220
Yes, I'll leave no stone unturned.

293
00:22:11,010 --> 00:22:12,930
You know what you should do.

294
00:22:12,930 --> 00:22:14,890
We'll get to it!

295
00:22:14,890 --> 00:22:18,600
Yeah, but if you find him,
don't do anything yet.

296
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:19,600
What?

297
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:23,940
Can't you see? We have to make
his father feel indebted to us.

298
00:22:23,940 --> 00:22:29,240
The longer he worries, the more he'll
appreciate us when we find Sabo.

299
00:22:29,780 --> 00:22:31,320
I see.

300
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:35,870
Until the time comes, don't do
anything - just monitor him.

301
00:22:35,870 --> 00:22:39,710
"We will have a visit this spring"?

302
00:22:39,710 --> 00:22:44,170
Dogra! Magra! Where is
the country called Goa?!

303
00:22:44,170 --> 00:22:48,760
Mt. Corvo, Gray Terminal,
and Windmill Village

304
00:22:48,760 --> 00:22:51,220
are part of Goa Kingdom supposedly.

305
00:22:51,220 --> 00:22:52,720
That's what I thought.

306
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,770
Easy, easy, boss.

307
00:22:54,770 --> 00:23:00,140
It's rare to see you reading a
newspaper. Hell must be freezing over.

308
00:23:00,140 --> 00:23:01,600
Ouch!

309
00:23:02,020 --> 00:23:05,140
Somebody's gonna visit the Kingdom?!

310
00:23:05,140 --> 00:23:08,440
It's making the headlines...

311
00:23:09,380 --> 00:23:13,150
What's going on here?
Are they that big a deal?

312
00:23:12,370 --> 00:23:16,990
A CELESTIAL DRAGON WILL VISIT

313
00:23:13,150 --> 00:23:15,460
These Celestial Dragons?

314
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:30,610
Curious after Luffy is taken in as an
apprentice, Ace and Sabo visit Naguri again.

315
00:23:30,610 --> 00:23:34,180
Seeing that the boys only care about
getting strong enough to beat a tiger,

316
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:36,930
Naguri tells them that they can't become
pirate captains just by being strong.

317
00:23:36,930 --> 00:23:40,440
What does it really take
to be a pirate captain?!

318
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:41,600
On the next episode of One Piece!

319
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:44,880
"The Battle against the Big Tiger!
Who is Going to be Captain?!"

320
00:23:44,880 --> 00:23:47,120
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
